text:
Driving all the way from New York, this place had been recommended by many of my friends.. To my surprise it was absolutely nothing like it was described. I was beyond disappointed being that I had driven a total of 3 and a half hours just to try these amazing "cheesesteaks" everyone always tells me about. Friday July 20th in the afternoon, I finally get in line to order and had to have been helped by the most disgusting person I've dealt with anywhere yet. And being that I'm from New York, I deal with a bunch of A******* on a daily already. As soon as I was about to finish placing my order I asked if I can PLEASE have extra cheese. And BEFORE my cheesesteak was even wrapped AND before they had started making my second order she said..RUDELY, "Well this one is already made." That response pissed me off, but whatever, in the moment I was hungry. Second cheesesteak was made, paid, sat, and started eating. I wasn't even given the right order. So after all that shitty service my order was messed up. And the way these were made, I most definitely did NOT get my money's worth. 

So after my shitty experience I walked across the street to GENO's and had a REAL Philly cheesesteak. I was finally content and very well satisfied I had finally gotten what I've been wanting to try now for over a year. So thank you GENO's. 

@yelp you should have an option for No Stars because that's how shitty that experience at Pat's was. They're definitely not the king of steaks.
